
Lopo de Brito was the second Captain of Portuguese Ceylon. Brito succeeded Jo&lt;U+00E3&gt;o da Silveira and was appointed in 1518 under Manuel I of Portugal, he was Captain until 1522. He was succeeded by Fern&lt;U+00E3&gt;o Gomes de Lemos.1
